1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP05]

3
00:01:41,159 --> 00:01:42,200
Stop right there!

4
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,120
Come and catch me!

5
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,560
I'm sorry!

6
00:01:58,319 --> 00:02:00,079
Apologies, I wasn't watching them.

7
00:02:01,359 --> 00:02:02,000
It's... it's fine.

8
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:13,039
I noticed that Cen Sisi

9
00:02:13,039 --> 00:02:14,560
has a lot of photos on social media

10
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:15,479
that copy your look.

11
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,080
What was on your mind?

12
00:02:43,919 --> 00:02:44,520
Thanks for

13
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,240
being quick on your feet back there.

14
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:47,719
I almost blew our cover.

15
00:02:50,319 --> 00:02:51,120
You are a natural.

16
00:02:53,199 --> 00:02:54,120
Well, do you think

17
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,120
I could make it to primetime?

18
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,159
Good enough to fool amateurs.

19
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,639
[Meaning... he's no amateur himself.]

20
00:03:03,199 --> 00:03:04,879
[Did I just make myself a joke in front of him?]

21
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,400
Chen Hui.

22
00:03:10,719 --> 00:03:12,080
Give Miss Ruan a ride in a bit.

23
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,319
Make sure to send Mr. Liu
a backup recording.

24
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:14,919
Got it.

25
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,159
Mr. Xu, aren't you heading back to the firm?

26
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:19,080
No, I'm heading to the airport.

27
00:03:20,639 --> 00:03:22,360
You're flying back to the States right now?

28
00:03:26,159 --> 00:03:26,800
So you...

29
00:03:27,919 --> 00:03:28,960
you came all this way

30
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,479
just for my case?

31
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,719
Do you think, Miss Ruan, that I

32
00:03:35,479 --> 00:03:36,639
have nothing better to do?

33
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,240
Thank you so much for

34
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,479
coming with me today.

35
00:03:47,439 --> 00:03:48,400
You must be up to your ears.

36
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:49,719
Take care of yourself.

37
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,520
Drive safe!

38
00:04:08,919 --> 00:04:09,599
"Hey, just wanna tell you"

39
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,479
"that I lost it back there."

40
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,080
"I didn't mean what I said."

41
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,280
"I didn't do any of those things."

42
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:17,399
"Are you still around Nanhu?"

43
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,079
She just figured out about being recorded.

44
00:04:20,319 --> 00:04:21,120
Nice try.

45
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,439
"Not around."

46
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:29,160
"We'll see each other in court."

47
00:04:56,399 --> 00:04:57,040
Coming!

48
00:04:59,000 --> 00:04:59,519
Hello.

49
00:04:59,839 --> 00:05:01,399
Hello, Mr. Xu.

50
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:03,279
It's for you.

51
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:05,079
Flowers for me?

52
00:05:05,199 --> 00:05:06,720
These are the flowers that you ordered.

53
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,360
And don't worry. The payment's already been made.

54
00:05:11,439 --> 00:05:12,800
Can I help you move in?

55
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,959
Sorry, no.

56
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:17,800
What's the problem?

57
00:05:18,439 --> 00:05:19,800
I just really don't need that.

58
00:05:20,079 --> 00:05:21,199
And do me a favor

59
00:05:21,199 --> 00:05:22,199
just throw them out.

60
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:23,399
No need?

61
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:27,040
Thank you.

62
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:28,800
Okay.
Bye!

63
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,319
Bye-bye, bye-bye!

64
00:05:42,079 --> 00:05:42,639
Hello?

65
00:05:43,079 --> 00:05:43,800
I didn't give you

66
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,000
my address so you could

67
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,040
cram my place with useless stuff.

68
00:05:46,439 --> 00:05:47,439
What stuff?

69
00:05:47,839 --> 00:05:49,240
A hideous plant.

70
00:05:51,519 --> 00:05:52,240
Hideous?

71
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:53,879
Ruan Yu picked it out

72
00:05:53,879 --> 00:05:55,120
as a gesture of gratitude.

73
00:05:55,319 --> 00:05:56,079
I figured

74
00:05:56,079 --> 00:05:57,720
bringing a little life into your place

75
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,759
wasn't such a bad idea.

76
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:00,920
And besides...

77
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,319
Sir, excuse me, sir?

78
00:06:07,439 --> 00:06:08,040
I'm sorry.

79
00:06:08,199 --> 00:06:09,839
Can you bring the flowers back to me?

80
00:06:10,439 --> 00:06:11,279
Why?

81
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:15,800
Thank you.

82
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,199
Fine, no why.

83
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:20,439
Bye-bye!
Bye.

84
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:25,680
That was very
generous.

85
00:06:26,439 --> 00:06:27,519
Did you return the favor?

86
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,399
Of course I did!

87
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,439
See? I sent him flowers.

88
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,519
He just signed for them.

89
00:06:38,839 --> 00:06:39,839
I knew it.

90
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:40,959
Romantic novelists

91
00:06:40,959 --> 00:06:42,079
special in "L'amour".

92
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,439
What kind of flowers?

93
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:46,079
Was it Cappuccino roses,

94
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:47,600
or Blue Enchantress?

95
00:06:48,639 --> 00:06:49,519
Carola's nice too.

96
00:06:51,439 --> 00:06:52,240
Widow's-thrill.

97
00:06:54,279 --> 00:06:55,480
Clears heat and detoxifies,

98
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,720
calms the mind and sharpens focus,

99
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,720
and helps with sleep.

100
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:58,439
He's always

101
00:06:58,439 --> 00:06:59,839
flying back and forth.

102
00:07:00,199 --> 00:07:01,519
Helps him with jet lag.

103
00:07:01,839 --> 00:07:02,800
Perfect for him.

104
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,199
Going the practical route, huh?

105
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,680
Nothing wrong with that.

106
00:07:09,639 --> 00:07:12,079
Was it just for him, or...?

107
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:16,560
Easy, take it slow.

108
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,560
It's not that heavy.

109
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:18,759
Where does this go?
Over there.

110
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,399
Okay, this corner.

111
00:07:20,399 --> 00:07:21,439
That corner, right?

112
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,639
What about the one from before?

113
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:32,839
"Thank you."

114
00:07:38,079 --> 00:07:39,120
"My pleasure, Mr. Xu."

115
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:42,920
"I'm putting together"

116
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:43,959
"the rest of the materials."

117
00:07:44,399 --> 00:07:45,959
"I might need your help again when I'm done."

118
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:49,879
"Don't mention it."

119
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:12,959
Grumpy fluff
needs me in the office.

120
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,279
No idea what kind of meltdown awaits.

121
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,240
Thank you, Miss Ruan,

122
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,279
for the money tree.

123
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,039
"What were you gonna say just now?"

124
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,399
"'Besides...' what?"

125
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:36,440
"I meant that Ruan Yu"

126
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,759
"ordered one for each of us."

127
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,360
"Couldn't exactly leave you out, could she?"

128
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,000
Terminate the contract?

129
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:27,159
You mean
we're dropping

130
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:29,159
Lily Vale's new book?

131
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:30,600
Do you have any idea

132
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,559
how many people have been

133
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,240
trashing us on our official page?

134
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,080
Accusing us of publishing

135
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,240
plagiarized work.

136
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:37,279
Shameless, they say.

137
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:38,600
Haven't we
already

138
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:40,159
cleared that up?

139
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,639
The Poet herself set the record straight.

140
00:09:42,759 --> 00:09:43,919
It's been Su Cheng

141
00:09:43,919 --> 00:09:44,720
stirring up drama,

142
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,799
smearing Lily Vale's name.

143
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:47,559
When there's public outrage,

144
00:09:47,919 --> 00:09:49,000
does truth really matter?

145
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,039
Of course it does!

146
00:09:50,279 --> 00:09:50,960
Otherwise,

147
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,039
what's the law even for?

148
00:09:52,399 --> 00:09:53,240
All this backlash

149
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,679
was intended upon by Su Cheng.

150
00:09:54,679 --> 00:09:56,360
Lily Vale is taking her to court.

151
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,720
The truth will out soon enough.

152
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,480
Let me be clear:

153
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:00,879
within three days,

154
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,320
if this plagiarism scandal

155
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,200
hasn't blown over,

156
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,440
we will end

157
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:06,600
all partnerships with Lily Vale.

158
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,080
Dropping Lily Vale at this point

159
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,480
is siding with Su Cheng.

160
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,240
That would destroy...

161
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,519
You'd better know when to stop.

162
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,559
I know she's a friend of yours, and that's why

163
00:10:15,559 --> 00:10:16,759
you're taking her side.

164
00:10:17,279 --> 00:10:18,480
But get this straight:

165
00:10:18,679 --> 00:10:20,399
it's Liwen that pays your salary,

166
00:10:20,399 --> 00:10:21,360
not Lily Vale.

167
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:28,080
If you want to talk about salaries...

168
00:10:29,519 --> 00:10:31,120
When I first joined Liwen,

169
00:10:31,799 --> 00:10:33,720
I was given absolutely nothing to work with.

170
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,399
Every author I believed in...

171
00:10:36,399 --> 00:10:37,840
The moment they showed any promise,

172
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,320
another editor would poach them.

173
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,639
It was Lily Vale who handed me

174
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:46,000
a manuscript everyone wanted

175
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,840
and said, "It's yours."

176
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,399
She trusted me completely.

177
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:51,039
She's not just a friend,

178
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:52,519
nor just a classmate.

179
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,559
She is the best partner

180
00:10:54,559 --> 00:10:55,639
I've ever had in my career.

181
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:57,879
Without her,

182
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:58,720
I would've
washed out of this industry.

183
00:11:02,679 --> 00:11:04,120
If I recall correctly,

184
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:06,399
you didn't get to where you are today

185
00:11:06,759 --> 00:11:08,559
without Lily Vale's help either.

186
00:11:12,559 --> 00:11:14,000
Yet here you are, losing all your senses,

187
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:14,919
burning bridges once across.

188
00:11:15,519 --> 00:11:17,279
who'd ever want to work with us again?

189
00:11:19,279 --> 00:11:20,360
Shen Mingying!

190
00:11:20,879 --> 00:11:22,799
You'd better watch what you say.

191
00:11:23,519 --> 00:11:24,960
Don't make yourself a target.

192
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,240
If being a target

193
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,759
means protection for Lily Vale,

194
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:30,600
this will be a role

195
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,159
gladly taken.

196
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:54,279
"The recording can only serve as"

197
00:11:54,279 --> 00:11:55,120
"supplementary evidence."

198
00:11:55,679 --> 00:11:57,440
"But the side-by-side analysis we initiated"

199
00:11:57,799 --> 00:11:59,080
"can establish the originality"

200
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:00,000
"of your novel."

201
00:12:00,759 --> 00:12:02,679
"Let's keep working through that."

202
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:04,559
"On it."

203
00:12:50,759 --> 00:12:51,559
Mr. Xu,

204
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:52,480
all set with
Chapter Thirteen.

205
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,039
I'll go over it again tonight.

206
00:13:00,039 --> 00:13:01,120
Sorry, I have to take this.

207
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:03,679
Hello?

208
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,279
At home.

209
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:09,759
Can't rule out retaliation

210
00:13:09,759 --> 00:13:10,840
from the defendant.

211
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:12,200
SG's top brass

212
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,440
should know better than anyone.

213
00:13:13,919 --> 00:13:14,720
The defendant is

214
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,480
capable of remotely detonating a bomb.

215
00:13:26,399 --> 00:13:27,600
That's a matter for the police.

216
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,960
Alright, handle it on your end.

217
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:37,759
Sorry about that.

218
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:41,720
Mr. Xu,

219
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,759
isn't it pretty late where you are?

220
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,279
Wasn't the caffeine doing the job?

221
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,480
What did you just say?

222
00:14:11,799 --> 00:14:13,759
I was asking if it's too late on your end.

223
00:14:13,759 --> 00:14:15,240
Are you okay to keep going?

224
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:19,639
Yeah, let's go.

225
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:32,320
Let's move on to Chapter Fourteen.

226
00:14:43,399 --> 00:14:46,200
Chapter Fourteen, paragraph three.

227
00:14:49,799 --> 00:14:50,759
He had never

228
00:14:50,759 --> 00:14:52,240
been fond of fuzzy animals.

229
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,840
Until the day he passed by the art museum

230
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:56,919
and saw her crouched in the bushes,

231
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,159
feeding a stray cat.

232
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:01,159
Sunlight. A gentle breeze.

233
00:15:01,679 --> 00:15:03,679
Green grass. A cat.

234
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,039
And her.

235
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:07,000
Taken together,

236
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,279
a sight of tenderness

237
00:15:08,279 --> 00:15:09,600
just short of heartbroken.

238
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,320
Softly, it landed right in his chest.

239
00:15:12,279 --> 00:15:13,039
From that day on,

240
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,000
as if contagious with this love,

241
00:15:16,039 --> 00:15:17,480
he began doing what she did —

242
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:19,679
saying hi to every fluffy

243
00:15:19,679 --> 00:15:20,440
on campus.

244
00:15:21,559 --> 00:15:22,519
Yet somehow,

245
00:15:23,399 --> 00:15:25,080
he could never manage to say that same word

246
00:15:25,759 --> 00:15:26,120
to her.

247
00:15:36,679 --> 00:15:38,480
He is a cat person after all.

248
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,080
I must've lost my mind

249
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,159
tweaking his persona like that.

250
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,120
These two lines match

251
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,519
pretty much word for word.

252
00:15:49,879 --> 00:15:50,519
Mr. Xu,

253
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:52,000
what's your take on this?

254
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,279
I think there are still some

255
00:15:54,279 --> 00:15:55,240
subtle differences.

256
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,120
You meant your male lead to love cats to the extent

257
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,039
that the female lead does.

258
00:15:58,639 --> 00:16:00,399
But in the other work, it isn't.

259
00:16:11,399 --> 00:16:12,200
I see it now.

260
00:16:12,679 --> 00:16:13,840
The Poet's male lead was well aware

261
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:14,600
when the female lead

262
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,639
would pass by the art museum

263
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,279
and staged the whole thing.

264
00:16:17,279 --> 00:16:18,080
So it's not a case
of love spilling over.

265
00:16:21,559 --> 00:16:22,679
I was reading it with assumptions.

266
00:16:23,039 --> 00:16:24,000
I forgot she'd rewritten him

267
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,159
as a calculating type.

268
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:28,759
"Calculating"...

269
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:30,639
... is a negative word, isn't it?

270
00:16:34,639 --> 00:16:35,200
Not really.

271
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:37,440
Mr. Xu, don't get the wrong idea again.

272
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:38,600
I'm not criticizing the male lead.

273
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,279
I'm being completely

274
00:16:40,279 --> 00:16:41,799
rational in this analysis.

275
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:43,159
"Calculating"...

276
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:46,200
It's more of a neutral term, really.

277
00:16:46,799 --> 00:16:47,720
On the positive side,

278
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:49,519
it just means the guy is clever.

279
00:17:00,919 --> 00:17:02,200
Is that coffee still hot?

280
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,360
Is he or she okay

281
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:04,039
over there?

282
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:05,759
It's not hot.

283
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:08,720
Come here.

284
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:14,119
How old is your cat?

285
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:15,599
Fully vaccinated?

286
00:17:16,039 --> 00:17:17,160
Okay to bathe right now?

287
00:17:17,599 --> 00:17:18,720
All vaccinations are done.

288
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:20,880
About six months old.

289
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,079
Okay then,

290
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,359
you should give he or she a wash.

291
00:17:24,759 --> 00:17:25,519
If the little one

292
00:17:25,519 --> 00:17:26,680
licked up some of the residue,

293
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:27,759
it could be harmful.

294
00:17:28,039 --> 00:17:28,839
We can resume
in a bit.

295
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:30,559
Alright.

296
00:17:37,839 --> 00:17:38,640
How do I do it?

297
00:17:39,359 --> 00:17:40,119
You don't know how?

298
00:17:43,839 --> 00:17:44,960
Isn't it your cat?

299
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,559
Then whose cat is staying with him?

300
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:53,640
So, how?

301
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:58,880
You'll need cat shampoo,

302
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:00,559
an absorbent towel,

303
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,119
and ideally a dryer too.

304
00:18:02,599 --> 00:18:04,160
Then place the cat in the tub

305
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,400
or the sink. Either works.

306
00:18:05,599 --> 00:18:06,680
Use water between

307
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:07,799
38 and 40 degrees.

308
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:08,759
- Make sure...
- Wait.

309
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,519
What do I do now?

310
00:18:25,759 --> 00:18:27,079
First, adjust the temperature.

311
00:18:27,359 --> 00:18:27,720
Do not

312
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:29,119
spray with the showerhead.

313
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:31,559
Fill the tub first.

314
00:18:31,799 --> 00:18:33,240
Keep the water level nice and shallow.

315
00:18:37,599 --> 00:18:38,640
Looks like the kitten's frightened.

316
00:18:38,839 --> 00:18:40,359
Be gentle with your movements.

317
00:18:48,240 --> 00:18:49,279
What do I do next?

318
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,440
With your left hand,
hold it gently by the scruff.

319
00:18:51,799 --> 00:18:53,079
Don't grip too hard.

320
00:19:01,519 --> 00:19:02,160
And then?

321
00:19:02,759 --> 00:19:04,160
Wet your fingers of the other hand,

322
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:05,519
[Little by little, dampen everything]

323
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:06,079
[below its neck]

324
00:19:06,079 --> 00:19:07,240
[before applying the shampoo.]

325
00:19:09,559 --> 00:19:11,119
[Make sure not to get water in its nose or mouth.]

326
00:20:25,519 --> 00:20:26,240
All clean.

327
00:20:29,079 --> 00:20:29,640
Good.

328
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:30,759
Mr. Xu,

329
00:20:30,759 --> 00:20:32,240
take that absorbent towel

330
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,160
and pat it dry,

331
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:34,519
then put it in the dryer.

332
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:35,920
Be gentle when you pat,

333
00:20:36,279 --> 00:20:37,440
and turn the dryer

334
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:38,119
down low.

335
00:21:38,519 --> 00:21:39,880
[So he likes cats too.]

336
00:21:41,799 --> 00:21:42,400
That's sweet.

337
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:27,599
Mr. Xu...

338
00:22:27,599 --> 00:22:28,960
I... I'm still here!

339
00:22:36,839 --> 00:22:37,480
Oh, I forgot.

340
00:22:47,759 --> 00:22:48,559
I need to shower.

341
00:22:50,799 --> 00:22:52,599
So, uh, Mr. Xu...

342
00:22:53,119 --> 00:22:54,240
Could you move me... I mean...

343
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,440
Uh... Can you take

344
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,680
the laptop out of the room?

345
00:22:57,079 --> 00:22:58,160
Can't you just end the video call?

346
00:22:59,799 --> 00:23:00,160
Right.
Right, right, right.

347
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:02,799
I, uh, I...

348
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:09,480
Oh my god! A shirtless man!

349
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,240
You scared me to death!

350
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:13,359
Xu Huaisong?

351
00:23:14,759 --> 00:23:15,400
What?
That's my question.

352
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:17,200
What's going on just now?

353
00:23:17,559 --> 00:23:17,920
I...
Spill it. Now.

354
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:21,519
What is there to spill?

355
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:23,240
His cat

356
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:24,920
knocked coffee all over him.

357
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:26,319
And he's awful at bathing cats,

358
00:23:27,359 --> 00:23:28,880
so he got soaked too.

359
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:30,119
That's the scene
you just walked in on.

360
00:23:35,119 --> 00:23:35,920
Wait, wait, wait.

361
00:23:36,559 --> 00:23:37,039
Something doesn't add up.

362
00:23:38,559 --> 00:23:39,119
Like what?

363
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:42,359
First, he has a cat.

364
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:43,720
Second, he has a cat but

365
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:44,680
doesn't know how to bathe it.
So who's the one

366
00:23:45,599 --> 00:23:46,480
that normally does it?

367
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:47,559
Are you saying that

368
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,279
there's someone else living with him?

369
00:23:52,559 --> 00:23:53,519
That he has a girlfriend?

370
00:23:55,039 --> 00:23:56,119
Or maybe he usually just

371
00:23:56,119 --> 00:23:57,480
takes the cat to a groomer.

372
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:58,799
But your hypothesis is

373
00:23:58,799 --> 00:23:59,680
not that far-fetched.

374
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:02,599
True.

375
00:24:04,119 --> 00:24:05,759
He has a dryer at home.

376
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:07,119
So someone

377
00:24:07,119 --> 00:24:08,960
probably has been bathing that cat at home.

378
00:24:12,119 --> 00:24:12,599
Besides,

379
00:24:12,599 --> 00:24:13,880
he's not exactly young anymore.

380
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:14,880
Accomplished guys like that

381
00:24:15,519 --> 00:24:17,039
hardly stay single.

382
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:18,559
Oh, actually, I have news.

383
00:24:18,559 --> 00:24:19,240
I almost forgot.
Good news.

384
00:24:20,799 --> 00:24:22,079
The official account for Qianhe

385
00:24:22,079 --> 00:24:23,200
just put out a statement,

386
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:26,200
concluding that a thorough investigation has led to

387
00:24:26,519 --> 00:24:27,519
The Poet's confession

388
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:29,480
that they weren't the original author,

389
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:30,799
Su Cheng's accusations

390
00:24:30,799 --> 00:24:32,680
are proven groundless.

391
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:33,839
So it's officially confirmed

392
00:24:34,079 --> 00:24:36,000
you are 100%

393
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,799
the original author.

394
00:24:37,799 --> 00:24:38,599
I sent you the link.
Take a look.

395
00:24:41,119 --> 00:24:42,240
I totally missed it just now.

396
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:44,000
"Please check out"

397
00:24:44,319 --> 00:24:45,119
"the official statement from Qianhe."
"Could this be used"

398
00:24:46,599 --> 00:24:47,799
"as supporting evidence"

399
00:24:47,799 --> 00:24:48,640
"in court?"
You should've seen

400
00:24:49,599 --> 00:24:51,240
the look on our editor-in-chief's face.

401
00:24:52,079 --> 00:24:53,000
Yesterday she was

402
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:54,480
rattling on and on

403
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:55,319
like a machine gun.
And today?

404
00:24:56,279 --> 00:24:57,039
On seeing the statement,

405
00:24:57,039 --> 00:24:58,680
she did a complete 180.

406
00:24:58,680 --> 00:24:59,839
Flipped faster than ever.

407
00:25:00,599 --> 00:25:02,400
I guess that's how you get to the top.

408
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:03,559
You gotta know when to bend.

409
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:07,279
Did you get into it with her again?

410
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:08,960
No way.

411
00:25:09,559 --> 00:25:10,960
I was making a reasoned argument.

412
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,440
She's the one who lost it.

413
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:16,160
Thanks for taking that bullet for me, girl.

414
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:16,759
No worries.

415
00:25:16,759 --> 00:25:17,880
Buy me dinner and we're even.

416
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,200
I'll buy you so many.

417
00:25:19,319 --> 00:25:19,799
Deal.

418
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,559
With this statement,

419
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,319
our chances just got a lot better.

420
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:27,720
But Cen Sisi just got

421
00:25:27,720 --> 00:25:29,200
publicly called out by the platform.

422
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:31,759
She'll probably spin up

423
00:25:31,759 --> 00:25:32,640
another army of trolls.

424
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,200
Easy-peasy.

425
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,200
Since we can't stop people from talking,

426
00:25:36,799 --> 00:25:38,160
we just close our own eyes.

427
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:39,519
Out of sight, out of mind.

428
00:25:46,119 --> 00:25:46,920
"Makes sense."

429
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:53,880
We barely put the curtain up

430
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:55,599
and Mr. Liu's already pulling it down.

431
00:25:56,359 --> 00:25:56,759
What?
Look.

432
00:25:57,559 --> 00:25:58,400
"Throwing Su Cheng under the bus"

433
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,440
"just to protect Lily Vale?"

434
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:00,400
"Dumb move."

435
00:26:00,519 --> 00:26:02,119
"The milky cow wins, obviously."

436
00:26:02,359 --> 00:26:03,160
"TBH,"
"her success"

437
00:26:03,839 --> 00:26:04,759
is sheer luck."

438
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:05,960
"Su Cheng's way better."

439
00:26:06,119 --> 00:26:06,759
"This world"

440
00:26:06,759 --> 00:26:07,799
"shall see justice."

441
00:26:08,079 --> 00:26:09,480
"I'm on Su Cheng's side."

442
00:26:09,839 --> 00:26:10,680
"Busy?"

443
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:12,000
"Not really."

444
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:14,559
"Write another version."

445
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,640
"This one barely has any punch."

446
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,359
"I'm not a putty in your hands."

447
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:22,279
"You only get one shot at a statement."

448
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:24,240
"If it doesn't hit right away,"

449
00:26:24,599 --> 00:26:25,920
"it's as good as a total loss."

450
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,559
"Tell me: what matters more?"

451
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,319
"Your client's interests or your pride?"

452
00:26:30,599 --> 00:26:31,480
"Easier of you to say."

453
00:26:34,359 --> 00:26:36,440
"I'm not joking this time, Mr. Liu."

454
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,000
"This really wasn't up to standard."

455
00:26:42,039 --> 00:26:43,480
"Can't argue with that."

456
00:26:43,839 --> 00:26:45,640
"I've been buried in cases."

457
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:46,759
"What were those"

458
00:26:47,359 --> 00:26:48,200
"screenshots again?"

459
00:27:01,559 --> 00:27:02,920
"The audio evidence is locked in."

460
00:27:03,359 --> 00:27:05,000
"We can go head-to-head with the defendant now."

461
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:06,799
"The statement"

462
00:27:06,799 --> 00:27:07,720
"was just the first step."

463
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:09,240
"Some public pushback"

464
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:10,480
"is expected."

465
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:11,440
"Don't sweat."

466
00:27:11,599 --> 00:27:13,359
"There's a legal statement following up."

467
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:14,599
"By the end of today,"

468
00:27:14,599 --> 00:27:16,279
"the narrative will make a U-turn."

469
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:19,200
Mr. Liu really doesn't seem to be cutting it.

470
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:22,079
Is he even reliable?

471
00:27:23,079 --> 00:27:23,640
On that front,

472
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:26,160
I'd say no one beats Mr. Xu.

473
00:27:26,839 --> 00:27:27,799
But it seems like he's

474
00:27:27,799 --> 00:27:28,839
already taken.

475
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:30,279
The way he texts you

476
00:27:30,279 --> 00:27:31,319
is so formal it hurts.

477
00:27:35,319 --> 00:27:36,000
Well then,

478
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:40,200
Well, I'll put on my diplomatic mask too.

479
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:42,200
"Alright."

480
00:27:42,319 --> 00:27:43,319
"Mr. Xu,"

481
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:45,000
"I can't thank you enough. Both of you."

482
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:53,960
"Noted."

483
00:28:02,319 --> 00:28:02,920
Remember

484
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:04,559
back when you were serializing?

485
00:28:04,559 --> 00:28:06,279
People showed up passive-aggressive all the time,

486
00:28:06,599 --> 00:28:07,680
saying Su Cheng's writing

487
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,119
was so much better than yours.

488
00:28:09,559 --> 00:28:11,160
You shrugged them away.

489
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:12,599
Quote unquote "different strokes"

490
00:28:12,599 --> 00:28:13,400
"for different folks,"

491
00:28:13,759 --> 00:28:14,480
and that

492
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:15,839
readers have the right to choose

493
00:28:15,839 --> 00:28:17,240
and leave their own opinions.

494
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,160
In hindsight,

495
00:28:18,319 --> 00:28:19,880
those were never real readers.

496
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:21,200
Must've been Cen Sisi's fake accounts,

497
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,559
running her own little puppet show.

498
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:24,920
Maybe.

499
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:26,680
What did you even do to her

500
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:28,000
to make her so obsessed with you

501
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:28,960
she wouldn't let go

502
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:30,720
after all these years?

503
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:32,920
If only I knew.

504
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:37,440
Was it about scholarship?

505
00:28:39,799 --> 00:28:40,839
Her recommendation spot?

506
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:46,960
Don't tell me you stole her man.

507
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:47,519
That can't be.

508
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:49,160
You've been single since birth.

509
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:55,319
Mingying.

510
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:57,640
Do you think this drama

511
00:28:58,400 --> 00:28:59,920
has something to do with Li Shican?

512
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:02,000
The way she talked about him

513
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:03,839
that day at the mall...

514
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:06,279
I guess she has a thing for him.

515
00:29:09,079 --> 00:29:10,400
Don't tell me all this trolling

516
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,160
and copycatting

517
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:13,079
was about you being her love rival?

518
00:29:14,599 --> 00:29:16,440
I don't have any feelings for that guy.

519
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:18,200
I'm more of an

520
00:29:18,799 --> 00:29:20,200
imaginary rival.

521
00:29:20,599 --> 00:29:21,279
Spot on.

522
00:29:22,319 --> 00:29:23,680
Come to think of it, Cen Sisi did

523
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:25,680
specifically bring up those good old days

524
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,079
back in the arts department.

525
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:28,440
With a whole lot of snark.

526
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,119
But that was so many years ago.

527
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:32,240
She can't still be hung up on it.

528
00:29:32,559 --> 00:29:33,440
Right?

529
00:29:34,119 --> 00:29:34,799
We haven't seen him

530
00:29:34,799 --> 00:29:35,880
in ages.

531
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:36,960
And he's now

532
00:29:37,279 --> 00:29:39,839
a full-blown hot-shot celebrity.

533
00:29:53,079 --> 00:29:53,759
Hey everyone!
I'm Li Shican.

534
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:55,680
Thank you all so much

535
00:29:55,680 --> 00:29:57,119
for joining my livestream today.

536
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,039
We just got started

537
00:29:59,039 --> 00:29:59,640
and I can already see

538
00:29:59,640 --> 00:30:00,799
our viewer count

539
00:30:00,799 --> 00:30:01,960
hitting a million.

540
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:03,720
Looks like today's giveaways

541
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:05,240
are a pretty big draw.

542
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:07,000
That's right. Today,

543
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:08,680
we're here to treat our "Starlights"

544
00:30:08,680 --> 00:30:09,599
to some special goodies.

545
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:11,200
We're playing a game with Shican:

546
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,480
Truth or Dare!

547
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:13,599
Shican,

548
00:30:13,599 --> 00:30:14,920
good for you.

549
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:16,000
Still so down-to-earth.

550
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:16,680
Truth or Dare

551
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:17,759
with your fans, huh?

552
00:30:17,759 --> 00:30:18,640
Everyone's here for it,

553
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:20,599
so let's all play together!

554
00:30:20,680 --> 00:30:21,039
Alright!

555
00:30:21,039 --> 00:30:23,000
So are you brave enough to take on the challenge?

556
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:23,759
Of course!

557
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:27,839
The statement had barely gone out when

558
00:30:28,119 --> 00:30:29,240
clickbait accounts' apologies

559
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:29,799
came rolling in.

560
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:32,039
And all the trolls on

561
00:30:32,039 --> 00:30:32,960
Cen Sisi's payroll

562
00:30:33,039 --> 00:30:34,160
have gone quiet.

563
00:30:37,119 --> 00:30:38,920
Xu Huaisong really delivers.

564
00:30:40,519 --> 00:30:41,079
Our editor-in-chief
was just nagging about

565
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:44,720
how positive your image is now.

566
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:46,240
Told me to push you to update

567
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:47,759
and ride this wave of attention.

568
00:30:48,519 --> 00:30:49,920
She always has it both ways.

569
00:30:53,920 --> 00:30:54,559
Go on, dig in.

570
00:30:54,559 --> 00:30:55,799
Here's how it works:

571
00:30:55,799 --> 00:30:58,119
everyone can drop a comment

